meta.content: A phylogeny of Delphinieae (Ranunculaceae) shows that Aconitum is nested within Delphinium and that Late Miocene transitions to long life cycles in the Himalayas and South West China coincide with bursts in diversification.

Jabbour F., & Renner S.S. 2011. A phylogeny of Delphinieae (Ranunculaceae) shows that Aconitum is nested within Delphinium and that Late Miocene transitions to long life cycles in the Himalayas and South West China coincide with bursts in diversification. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, .
